race.comment: BAVETTE (1) scored two runs back then was well in commission last time but could only manage to finish sixth over 1450m at Kilmore after he was in the firing line on the turn. This is a nice drop in grade and gets his chance. MAGIC SPEED (11) was out of the money two runs back then again missed the frame last start over 1000m at Randwick, beaten 0.8 lengths into fifth. Has her share of talent and is a top-three prospect. NIGHTS INFERNO (5) scored a long overdue win over this trip at the Sapphire Coast and can go on with it now. MAZ KANATA (3) finds an easier race to what she was contesting last start at Gosford. Keep safe. Small field but an open affair. MAJESTUOUSO PHOENIX (2) next elect third run from a spell.
